        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 6:10PM EDT by NWS Newport/Morehead City NC</headline>
        <description>At 608 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Bruce, or 7 miles northeast of Farmville, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts 40 to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Parmele, Beargrass, Bell Arthur, House, Pitt Greenville Airport,
Everetts, Robersonville, Bruce, Stokes, Falkland, Hamilton, Bethel,
Smithwick, Hassell, Gold Point, Farmville, Williamston, and
Greenville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
